    "body": "Hi maintainers — I have opened a draft PR (#7495) that surfaces the underlying pest parse error at the two log sites that previously dropped it (`git_status.rs::format_text` and the `status.format` branch in `status.rs`), and aligns the third site (`status.pipestatus_segment_format`) to use Display formatting for visual consistency. The pest renderer attached to `StringFormatterError::Parse` already produces a position-aware diagnostic naming the rules it expected, so for `stashed = \" ${count}$\"` the warn now shows the column and what was expected — which makes the \"needs escaping\" cause obvious without us hard-coding a starship-specific hint string. Happy to adjust the wording or scope; flagging here so anyone else looking at this issue knows it is being worked on.\n",
